Mod-8mm has 2 licenses:<br />
"MIT License" for programming code.<br />
"CC-BY 4.0" Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International for documents.<br />
Formal statements are in files LICENSE-CODE-MIT and LICENSE-DOCUMENTS-CC-BY.<br /><br />

Informal statement<br />
For all or substantial use of Mod-8mm code include or keep existing comments like:<br />
Mod-8mm Project code applies the Open Source "MIT License"<br />
Copyright (C) 2026 John Calder some rights reserved<br />
https://choosealicense.com/licenses/mit/<br /><br />

For minor use of Mod-8mm code and any use of Mod-8mm documents, acknowledge "mod-8-film.com".<br />
Examples:<br />
Sources include mod-8-film.com<br />
Acknowledgement: mod-8-film.com<br />
mod-8-film.com<br /><br />

In many cases, acknowledgements are already in the code and in photos, diagrams in our documents. You only need to leave them there.
